e life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan was born about 1486, in England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Robert Pytfolde."},"et":{"abt 1486–":"umbes 1486–Surnud","1478–Male":"1478–Surnud","1501–Male":"1501–Surnud","1486–Female":"1486–Surnud","1501":"1501","1478":"1478","1486":"1486","abt 1486":"umbes 1486","Allington, Dorsetshire, England, United Kingdom":"Allington, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt 1486–":"noin 1486–Kuollut","1478–Male":"1478–Kuollut","1501–Male":"1501–Kuollut","1486–Female":"1486–Kuollut","1501":"1501","1478":"1478","1486":"1486","abt 1486":"noin 1486","Allington, Dorsetshire, England, United Kingdom":"Allington, Dorset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"abt 1486–":"environ 1486–Décédée","1478–Male":"1478–Décédé","1501–Male":"1501–Décédé","1486–